         <abstract>
             <para>This document explains how to install and configure
                 <application>ufmcontrol</application>.
             </para>
         </abstract>
    </articleinfo>
    <sect1 id="building-and-installing">
        <title>Building And Installing</title>
        <para>
            If you do not use the port (see <xref linkend="port">),
            you can type the following as root:
         </para>
         <screen>&prompt.root; <userinput>make && make install</userinput></screen>
         <para>or (as normal user):</para>
         <screen>&prompt.user; <userinput>make && make install PREFIX=/where/to/install</userinput></screen>
         <para>In the latter case, you must also set the variables:</para>
         <para>
	     <programlisting>LD_LIBRARY_PATH=<replaceable>/where/to/install/lib</replaceable></programlisting>
             <programlisting>NLSPATH=<replaceable>'/where/to/install/share/nls/%L/ufmcontrol.cat'</replaceable></programlisting>
         </para>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 id="about-i18n-l10n-support">
        <title>About I18N/L10N Support</title>
        <para>If you want to type commands and see messages in your
              language, you must set the environment variable LANG
              (and possibly TERM) to a suitable value, e.g. (for Russian):
        </para>
	<para>
        <programlisting>LANG=<replaceable>ru_RU.KOI8-R</replaceable></programlisting>
        <programlisting>TERM=<replaceable>cons25r</replaceable></programlisting>
        </para>
        <para>Currently, only the following languages are supported:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem><para>Bulgarian</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Dutch</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>English (default)</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>French</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>German</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Italian</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Spanish</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Romanian</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Russian</para></listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 id="port">
        <title>Installing Via Port</title>
        <para>First download the <application>shar</application> <ulink url="http://ufmcontrol.sourceforge.net/ports/audio/ufmcontrol.shar">file</ulink>,
    	and copy it under <filename>/usr/ports/audio</filename>;
	then build and install <application>ufmcontrol</application>
	with these commands:</para>
        <screen>&prompt.root; <userinput>sh ./ufmcontrol.shar</userinput></screen>
        <screen>&prompt.root; <userinput>cd <filename>ufmcontrol-i18n</filename></userinput></screen>
        <screen>&prompt.root; <userinput>make install clean</userinput></screen>
	<note><para>Since 5 October 2003, ufmcontrol is part of the FreeBSD Ports Collection,
	so the directory <filename>/usr/ports/audio/ufmcontrol-i18n</filename> should
	already be present on your system.</para></note>
    </sect1>
